Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveAfter they invaded a section of the international airport in Kaduna o Saturday, bandits moved a bit further on Monday.
They planted IEDSs along the Kaduna-Abuja rail, leading to a Kaduna-bound train derailing on Monday after an explosion around Katari, Kaduna State.
The 6pm train which took off from Idu train station at the Federal Capital Territory Monday hit an explosives device about 30 minutes to Rigasa train station in Kaduna.
Security agents have been mobilised to the area to rescue the passengers.
There has been no official statement since the incident.
